The brimstone key is a key obtained from killing monsters while on a Slayer task given by Konar quo Maten. It is used to open the brimstone chest. The average value of a drop from the brimstone chest is 115,308.02. Upon death in the Wilderness, a brimstone key converts to two coins for the killer.

The probability of receiving a key as a drop increases with the slain monster's Combat level. For monsters with combat level 100 or higher, the probability is between 1 / 100 {\displaystyle 1/100} and 1 / 50 {\displaystyle 1/50} , scaling linearly and capping at level 350. Specifically, the probability for a monster with combat level L {\displaystyle L} is[1]

1 120 − ⌊ L / 5 ⌋ {\displaystyle {\frac {1}{120-\left\lfloor L/5\right\rfloor }}} .

For monsters with combat level L {\displaystyle L} smaller than level 100, the probability follows the curve[2]

1 100 + ⌊ ( 100 − L ) 2 / 5 ⌋ {\displaystyle {\frac {1}{100+\left\lfloor (100-L)^{2}/5\right\rfloor }}} .

Additionally, if the monster has a Slayer level requirement, there is a 20% boost in the drop probability.[3]

The '''brimstone key''' is a key obtained from killing monsters while on a [[Slayer task]] given by [[Konar quo Maten]]. It is used to open the [[brimstone chest]]. The average value of a drop from the brimstone chest is {{Coins|{{KDTValue}}}}. Upon [[death]] in the [[Wilderness]], a brimstone key converts to two [[coins]] for the killer.

The probability of receiving a key as a drop increases with the slain monster's [[Combat level]]. For monsters with combat level 100 or higher, the probability is between <math>1/100</math> and <math>1/50</math>, scaling linearly and capping at level 350. Specifically, the probability for a monster with combat level <math>L</math> is{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Kieren|url=https://twitter.com/JagexKieren/status/1083781544135847936|date=16 January 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/g6A5h|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=It follows a curve up until level 100 then scales linearly between those 2 values upto level 350 combat. Creatures over thsi{{sic}} will cap at 1/50. [https://pbs.twimg.com/media/DwpdLK2W0AEynZy.jpg]}} 
:<math>\frac{1}{120 - \left\lfloor L/5 \right\rfloor}</math>.
For monsters with combat level <math>L</math> smaller than level 100, the probability follows the curve{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Kieren|url=https://twitter.com/JagexKieren/status/1083783815141707781|date=16 January 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/G2QQq|archivedate=29 April 2020|quote=0.2*(CBLEVEL - 100)^2 + 100}} 
:<math>\frac{1}{100 + \left\lfloor (100 - L)^2/5 \right\rfloor}</math>.
Additionally, if the monster has a [[Slayer]] level requirement, there is a 20% boost in the drop probability.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269996125387460608|date=8 June 2020|archiveurl=http://archive.is/mRtA0|archivedate=11 June 2020}}
